Warrant officer Sipho Mthetwa was shot and killed during a police chase in the area on Wednesday night. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Police Commissioner Deliwe de Lange has condemned the killing of a police officer in Vosloorus on the East Rand.Warrant Officer Sipho Mthetwa was shot and killed during a police chase in the area on Wednesday night.He and other officers were on their routine patrols when they spotted a suspicious vehicle fitted with false registration numbers. On approaching the vehicle, one of three suspects jumped out of the vehicle and opened fire, instantly killing Mthetwa.Two suspects were arrested, while the third managed to flee on foot.The police's Lungelo Dlamini says: We managed to arrest two suspects and recovered a licence. The investigation continues. We are following several leads to arrest the other suspect. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)